                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d436">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94 Commission/118a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Shanghai (<persName corresp="#p_CES1" type="to"
                            >Cunningham</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-20T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 20, 1932—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>43. Reference Department’s February 5, 6 p.m. In response to a request received
                    from the Secretary of the Council of the League<note n="82" xml:id="d436fn82"
                        >Not printed.</note> the Department desires that you continue to cooperate
                    with the League Shanghai Committee in preparing as soon as possible a report on
                    present events. You should follow the procedure indicated in the Department’s
                    previous instruction above referred to. Report action taken, and repeat to
                    Nanking.</p>
                <p>Inform Minister.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
